**Item #:** SCP-7000
 
**Object Class:** Euclid
 
**Special Containment Procedures:**  A containment zone has been established between the former office of Ian Vance and the newly reconstructed hallway to the northern wing of Site-74, including the office itself. All hallways leading into the containment zone are currently in the process of being walled off and a make-shift secure entrance is being created for testing purposes. 

D-Class testing is to start at the beginning of each week and result in the least one victim, creating a temporary safe zone for a period of at least 20 hours.[[footnote]] These periods of time have varied but have yet to exceed 40 hours. [[/footnote]] During this period of time, Site-74 personnel are instructed to move any anomalous or otherwise important objects from the remainder of the northern wing. Salt barriers, protective sigils, and banishment wards are to be utilized in the area surrounding the containment zone to increase the duration of the safe period. One (1) D-Class personnel must refresh these protective elements daily, in accordance with the guidelines set by Site-74's medium, Imogen Calloway.

**Description:** SCP-7000 is a non-sentient supernatural entity, believed to be the spirit of former Senior Researcher, Ian Vance, who was killed in a containment breach 8 months prior to the first documented sighting of SCP-7000. SCP-7000 has been shown to recreate the moments of its death at irregular intervals. These events have been shown to last no longer than 15 minutes, and occur in the area between the former office of Ian Vance and the newly reconstructed hallway to the northern wing of Site-74. 

Any personnel in the direct path between the two locations during an SCP-7000 Bludgeoning event will suffer intense blunt force trauma resulting in their death. Injury patterns have been shown to be unique to the space the victim is occupying between the two locations, indicating that two victims standing in the same location during two separate events will result in nearly identical injuries sustained, with variations to be expected in regards to muscle mass and body type. This was later confirmed via D-Class testing. 

Due to the current layout of the northern wing entrance, Bludgeoning events are able to be witnessed by outside observers, and updated construction will provide a viewing area for testing. Camera and audio equipment within range during a Bludgeoning event will likely fail, producing static, warping images, or shutting off completely. As has been noted with previous paranormal anomalies, inconsistent battery life has been noted during any SCP-7000 activity.

**Addendum-1:** Discovery 
On January 16th, 2021, Site Director Isreal Ray was found crushed to death in front of the office of Ian Vance. An investigation was launched into his death, limiting personnel entry to the area. An autopsy suggested the cause of death via blunt force trauma in line with being crushed by falling rubble. All camera footage of the event was highly distorted, which lead to the investigation concluding the event was paranormal in nature. MTF-59 “Greater Ghost” was sent to investigate the area more thoroughly during non-operational hours.

